# LaTeX — PEF papers

## Language

British English: recognised, behaviour, rigour, optimisation, generalised.

## Maths

- Greek in math mode: `$\eta$`, `$\kappa$`, `$\rho$`, `$\psi$` — not Unicode κ, ρ
- Display: `\begin{equation}...\end{equation}` with `\label{eq:...}`; cite `\ref{eq:...}`
- Fractions: `\frac{}{}`; subscripts with braces: `$\sigma^2_A$`

## Structure

- One `\section` per file under `sections/`; `main.tex` only inputs and preamble
- Generated counts: `\input{scripts/paper_pipeline/outputs/numbers.tex}` (empirical) — never hand-edit macro values that pipeline owns

## Tone

Modest claims; statistics or citations for empirical statements. Distribution-free η in empirical; Gaussian MI link labelled as (A1)–(A2).

